## Other useful commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `npm run dev` | Start Vite dev server (web client) |
| `npm run build` | Build frontend only |
| `npm run electron:dev` | Run Electron app in dev mode (local-only build + launch) |
| `npm run electron:local` | Same as electron:dev (extract schema, build, launch) |
| `npm run electron:installer` | Build production installer → `release/` (no version bump, no publish) |
| `npm run github:clean-releases` | Delete old GitHub releases (keeps latest 10; use `-- --keep 5` to keep 5). Saves repo storage. Requires `GH_TOKEN` or `GITHUB_TOKEN`. |
| `npm run prepare-local-db` | Rewrite tenant/user IDs in existing DB for local-only use |
| `npm run clear-local-transactions` | Clear transactions (and related data) from local DB |
| `npm run db:migrate:lan` | Run **PostgreSQL** migrations in `database/migrations/` (uses root `.env` → `DATABASE_URL`) |
| `npm run migrate:sqlite-to-postgres` | Copy tenant data from **SQLite backup** → PostgreSQL (default path: `F:\DB Backup pbookspro\rkbuilders_14_3_2026_backup_20260329_142110`; override with `--sqlite` or `SQLITE_BACKUP_PATH`) |
| `npm run migrate:sqlite-to-postgres:transactions` | Re-import **transactions** only for the target tenant (same defaults) |
| `npm run repair:pg-categories` | Repair `category_id` on bills/transactions in PostgreSQL from the same SQLite backup (same defaults) |
| `npm run dev:backend` | Start **Express API** in dev (`tsx watch`, reload on change) — `http://localhost:3000/api` |
| `npm run build:backend` | Compile `backend/` TypeScript → `backend/dist/` |
| `npm run start:backend` | Run compiled API (`node backend/dist/index.js`) |

