## Clean old GitHub releases (save storage)

To remove old releases and free repo storage:

```powershell
npm run github:clean-releases
```

This keeps the **latest 10 releases** (by publish date) and deletes the rest. The command loads `.env`, so set `GH_TOKEN` or `GITHUB_TOKEN` there (same as for deploy) with `repo` scope.

To keep a different number (e.g. 5):

```powershell
npm run github:clean-releases -- --keep 5
```

Deleting a release removes the release and its assets (e.g. .exe, blockmap). Git tags are not deleted.
